{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015sCCiwMXbpnk7XRXMqAL48","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me create a comprehensive report:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've found all code related to the \"Prompts\" section in the project info page. Here's what's implemented:\n\n### 1. **Backend Handler - Prompts API Endpoint**\nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\nThe backend has two key handlers:\n\n- **`handleAPIProjectInfo` (lines 939-1025)**: Returns project info including `prompt_files` array with git history\n  - Reads all files from `.cloche/prompts/` directory\n  - Runs `git log --follow` for each prompt file to fetch commit history\n  - Returns structured data: `SHA`, `Date`, `Message` for each commit\n\n- **`handleAPIPromptDiff` (lines 1027-1056)**: Fetches git diff for a specific prompt file at a specific commit\n  - Takes `file` and `sha` query parameters\n  - Runs `git diff sha^..sha -- file` to show what changed in that commit\n  - Returns the diff as plain text\n\n### 2. **Frontend UI - Project Detail Template**\nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n\nThe UI has a \"Prompt Files\" section (lines 98-117) that:\n\n- **Renders expandable sections** using HTML `<details>` elements (native browser expansion)\n  - Each prompt file path is in a `<summary>` tag (shows the file path with a disclosure triangle)\n  - When expanded, shows git commit history\n\n- **Commit history rendering** (lines 104-109):\n  - Each commit is rendered as a `<div class=\"prompt-commit\">` with:\n    - Short SHA (7 chars) as a clickable link\n    - Date (formatted as YYYY-MM-DD)\n    - Commit message\n  - Has `data-file` and `data-sha` attributes to identify which file/commit was clicked\n\n- **Expansion arrow behavior**:\n  - Native `<details>/<summary>` elements provide built-in expand/collapse\n  - No custom expansion arrows - browser's default disclosure triangle\n\n### 3. **Frontend JavaScript - Diff Toggle**\nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 123-139)\n\nThe `toggleDiff(el)` function handles expanding/collapsing diffs:\n\n- **Toggle behavior**:\n  - Checks if a diff block already exists below the commit element\n  - If exists: removes it (collapse)\n  - If not exists: fetches and inserts it (expand)\n\n- **Diff fetching** (line 131):\n  - Calls `/api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file={file}&sha={sha}`\n  - Receives plain text diff output\n  - Wraps in `<pre class=\"diff-block\">` element\n\n- **DOM insertion**:\n  - Inserts diff block as a sibling right after the commit line\n  - Uses `el.parentNode.insertBefore()` for precise placement\n\n### 4. **CSS Styling**\nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n\nStyling for the prompts section (lines 198-221):\n\n- **Details/Summary styling** (lines 198-207):\n  - `details` element has margin and padding\n  - `summary` is styled with a cursor pointer and font styling\n  - Creates the expandable section appearance\n\n- **Diff block styling** (lines 551-563):\n  - `.diff-block`: Pre-formatted code display with monospace font\n  - Max-height of 300px with overflow auto\n  - Styled to match the overall design with border and rounded corners\n\n### File Locations\n\n**Backend**:\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 939-1056)\n\n**Frontend Templates**:\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 89-139)\n\n**Styling**:\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` (lines 198-221, 551-563)\n\nThe implementation uses native HTML `<details>` elements for the initial prompt file expansion and custom JavaScript to handle the nested diff toggle functionality."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aa774aa2f9fe70661 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 61619\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 28807</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cd1b14cf-06c4-4c38-9c6b-7ee6a915d4c8","uuid":"52707863-cbf0-4c80-8367-832864382370","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all code related to the \"Prompts\" section in a project info page. Look for:\n1. Any TUI/UI code that renders a \"Prompts\" section with expansion arrows\n2. Code that handles expanding/collapsing prompts to show content\n3. Any code that fetches prompt file contents vs git commits\n\nSearch broadly - check for terms like \"Prompts\", \"prompt\", \"expansion\", \"expand\", \"collapse\", \"toggle\" in UI/TUI code. Also look for any bubbletea or terminal UI components. Check internal/adapters/, cmd/, and any UI-related directories.","agentId":"aa774aa2f9fe70661","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information. Let me create a comprehensive report:\n\n## Summary\n\nI've found all code related to the \"Prompts\" section in the project info page. Here's what's implemented:\n\n### 1. **Backend Handler - Prompts API Endpoint**\nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\nThe backend has two key handlers:\n\n- **`handleAPIProjectInfo` (lines 939-1025)**: Returns project info including `prompt_files` array with git history\n  - Reads all files from `.cloche/prompts/` directory\n  - Runs `git log --follow` for each prompt file to fetch commit history\n  - Returns structured data: `SHA`, `Date`, `Message` for each commit\n\n- **`handleAPIPromptDiff` (lines 1027-1056)**: Fetches git diff for a specific prompt file at a specific commit\n  - Takes `file` and `sha` query parameters\n  - Runs `git diff sha^..sha -- file` to show what changed in that commit\n  - Returns the diff as plain text\n\n### 2. **Frontend UI - Project Detail Template**\nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n\nThe UI has a \"Prompt Files\" section (lines 98-117) that:\n\n- **Renders expandable sections** using HTML `<details>` elements (native browser expansion)\n  - Each prompt file path is in a `<summary>` tag (shows the file path with a disclosure triangle)\n  - When expanded, shows git commit history\n\n- **Commit history rendering** (lines 104-109):\n  - Each commit is rendered as a `<div class=\"prompt-commit\">` with:\n    - Short SHA (7 chars) as a clickable link\n    - Date (formatted as YYYY-MM-DD)\n    - Commit message\n  - Has `data-file` and `data-sha` attributes to identify which file/commit was clicked\n\n- **Expansion arrow behavior**:\n  - Native `<details>/<summary>` elements provide built-in expand/collapse\n  - No custom expansion arrows - browser's default disclosure triangle\n\n### 3. **Frontend JavaScript - Diff Toggle**\nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 123-139)\n\nThe `toggleDiff(el)` function handles expanding/collapsing diffs:\n\n- **Toggle behavior**:\n  - Checks if a diff block already exists below the commit element\n  - If exists: removes it (collapse)\n  - If not exists: fetches and inserts it (expand)\n\n- **Diff fetching** (line 131):\n  - Calls `/api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file={file}&sha={sha}`\n  - Receives plain text diff output\n  - Wraps in `<pre class=\"diff-block\">` element\n\n- **DOM insertion**:\n  - Inserts diff block as a sibling right after the commit line\n  - Uses `el.parentNode.insertBefore()` for precise placement\n\n### 4. **CSS Styling**\nFile: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`\n\nStyling for the prompts section (lines 198-221):\n\n- **Details/Summary styling** (lines 198-207):\n  - `details` element has margin and padding\n  - `summary` is styled with a cursor pointer and font styling\n  - Creates the expandable section appearance\n\n- **Diff block styling** (lines 551-563):\n  - `.diff-block`: Pre-formatted code display with monospace font\n  - Max-height of 300px with overflow auto\n  - Styled to match the overall design with border and rounded corners\n\n### File Locations\n\n**Backend**:\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 939-1056)\n\n**Frontend Templates**:\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (lines 89-139)\n\n**Styling**:\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` (lines 198-221, 551-563)\n\nThe implementation uses native HTML `<details>` elements for the initial prompt file expansion and custom JavaScript to handle the nested diff toggle functionality."}],"totalDurationMs":28807,"totalTokens":61619,"totalToolUseCount":18,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":311,"cache_read_input_tokens":60295,"output_tokens":1008,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":311},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
