{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Xj46bXzvPBXzNfPTNWJLdJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`prompt_files` is `null` in the JSON. The handler is finding `dir=/tmp/TestAPIProjectInfo_PromptFileContents4114011450/001`, `promptsDir` would be `/tmp/TestAPIProjectInfo_PromptFileContents4114011450/001/.cloche/prompts`. But the test is creating the file correctly. Let me check...\n\nWait, `prompt_files` is null, not empty array. In Go, `json.Marshal(nil)` produces `null`, so this means `promptFiles` stayed nil - the `os.ReadDir` must have returned an error.\n\n\nThe paths should match since the test writes to the same `.cloche/prompts` directory that the handler reads from, but the nil slice suggests `os.ReadDir` either failed, filtered out all entries as directories, or never appended anything to the slice.\n\nLooking at the git log call - that's the culprit. The handler runs `git log --follow` in the temp directory, which isn't a git repo, so the command fails and the handler skips the file entirely with `continue`. The fix is to still add the prompt file to the results even when git log fails, just with an empty history instead of abandoning it completely. This same issue would affect production too if a prompt file has never been committed.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":324,"cache_read_input_tokens":46279,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":324},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cd1b14cf-06c4-4c38-9c6b-7ee6a915d4c8","uuid":"2c608d67-3da6-489f-a400-10d4bb79da4c"}
